lyrics:
In the deep of night, the mice do creep,
While cats sharpen claws, in shadows they seep.
In a dance of darkness, within the city's sprawl,
They battle endlessly, no mercy, no truce at all.

Felines flaunt their teeth, sharp and keen,
Mice, with cunning, plot unseen.
Through cracks in homes and alleys tight,
The war rages on, an endless fight.
